# Syntax

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  // Side effect code here
});
```

By default, `useEffect` runs **after every render** (both initial and subsequent updates).

## Example: Update Document Title

```jsx
import { useEffect, useState } from 'react';

function TitleUpdater() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  useEffect(() => {
    document.title = `You clicked ${count} times`;
  });

  return (
    <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>
      Clicked {count} times
    </button>
  );
}
```

After every render (including the initial one), the effect runs and updates the title.

